Yes — the most likely cause was the slope-family winner gate. In the prior file, the candidate loop would `continue` whenever `slope` or `intercept` stayed `na`, and the winner logic only promoted a slope family when `votes > winningVotes`; that can fail when the only available family has just its initial vote, which leaves the main channel undrawn while orphan rails can still accumulate from other logic.[^7_1]

I fixed that by changing the slope-family winner test from `>` to `>=`, so the first valid pivot-pair slope bin can become the active winner immediately instead of being skipped.[^7_1]

